 Europe before the twelfth century and redefines how medievalists should teach the history of Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAffect (Psychology)xReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aMonasticism and religious orders. 0aPietyxHistoryy11th century. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAbbey of Fécamp.  aAffective piety.  aBenedictines.  aConfessio theologica.  aHistory of emotion.  aJohn of Fécamp, abbot.  aMedieval Christianity.  aMedieval devotion.  aMonasticism.  aNormandy.1 aMancia, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614021040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526140210423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526140210/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles